headline: Consumers Energy Foundation Awards $100,000 to Mid-Michigan Nonprofit for 2025 People Awards
summary: The Consumers Energy Foundation unveiled EightCAP, a Mid-Michigan nonprofit, as one of its 2025 People Award winners today, distributing $100,000 to launch its Household Goods for Rehousing Success project.

headline: Consumers Energy Foundation Awards $150,000 to Jackson Nonprofit for 2025 People Awards
summary: The Consumers Energy Foundation unveiled Michigan AFL-CIO Workforce Development Institute (WDI) in Jackson as one of its 2025 People Award winners today, distributing $150,000 to the nonprofit to support a new Jackson area workforce cohort for its Access for All program.

headline: Consumers Energy Foundation Awards $150,000 to Kalamazoo Nonprofit for 2025 People Awards
summary: The Consumers Energy Foundation unveiled Community Homeworks in Kalamazoo as one of its 2025 People Award winners today, distributing $150,000 to the area nonprofit to help empower its neighbors to maintain safe, stable and sustainable homes.

headline: Consumers Energy Foundation Awards $100,000 to Saginaw Nonprofit for 2025 People Awards
summary: The Consumers Energy Foundation unveiled the East Side Soup Kitchen (ESSK) in Saginaw as one of its 2025 People Award winners today, distributing $100,000 to the area nonprofit to support infrastructure improvements that will increase their capacity.
